```

This test verifies that 'Restore approvals' survives a config reload (same process). The new test must verify it survives a **dev proxy hot reload** (worker kill + fork).

The existing test uses `startMcpServer(configDir, true, undefined, { OPENTABS_DANGEROUSLY_SKIP_PERMISSIONS: '1' })` — the second arg `true` enables hot mode (dev proxy). The `server.triggerHotReload()` method sends SIGUSR1 to the proxy, which kills the old worker and forks a new one.

Pattern from existing E2E tests:
```typescript
server.triggerHotReload();
await waitForLog(server, 'Hot reload complete', 20_000);
```

